SIMPLE: daubing
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Daubing
<hw>Daub"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of one who
daubs; that which is daubed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A rough coat of mortar put upon a wall to give it
the appearance of stone; rough-cast.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>In currying, a mixture of fish oil and tallow worked
into leather; -- called also <altname>dubbing</altname>.</def>
<rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Daubreelite</ent>⟦br⟧
